  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study was done with the primary aim of assessing the efficacy (as calculated by pain
      intensity difference) of patient controlled regional analgesia (PCRA) technique against oral
      analgesics, which has been the standard of care at our hospital. Secondary objectives were to
      analyze the volume and dose of LA that should be given, patient satisfaction and the
      long-term outcome for patients treated with the PCRA technique.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
